She carries it around

1126
01:13:03,920 --> 01:13:06,720
Bananas withered at the tips
Gushing stream breaks them in halves

1127
01:13:06,840 --> 01:13:08,840
One is left
She carries it around

1128
01:13:10,840 --> 01:13:12,279
Damn! This is the whole cluster!

1129
01:13:14,560 --> 01:13:16,560
-You bananas!
-You withered!

1130
01:13:17,640 --> 01:13:19,720
-You rot fruit!
-You bland!

1131
01:13:20,520 --> 01:13:22,520
-You tasteless!
-Rot body!

1132
01:13:22,920 --> 01:13:24,720
-Green bitch!
-Ugly banana!

1133
01:13:25,359 --> 01:13:26,479
-Yucky!

1134
01:13:27,479 --> 01:13:28,960
Stinky!

1135
01:13:29,760 --> 01:13:31,119
Damn, you twats!

1136
01:13:31,279 --> 01:13:32,680
I came here to scare you.

1137
01:13:32,760 --> 01:13:34,960
Not for you to insult me
and leave me hanging, freaks!

1138
01:13:35,119 --> 01:13:36,439
You called us freaks, bitch?

1139
01:13:36,520 --> 01:13:38,840
-What's your problem?
-Come on, fat ass!

1140
01:13:39,119 --> 01:13:41,840
I was a wife of a warrior, assholes!

1141
01:13:43,159 --> 01:13:45,640
My plan as a headless ghost works!
They're all freaked out.

1142
01:13:45,840 --> 01:13:47,560
-Em and Ood?
-They'll be here.

1143
01:13:47,800 --> 01:13:49,880
Trust me. They're not going anywhere.

1144
01:13:51,239 --> 01:13:52,880
They'll be scared shitless.

1145
01:13:53,039 --> 01:13:55,920
Just wait for my headless ghost.

1146
01:13:57,119 --> 01:13:59,439
Song, where are those two?

1147
01:13:59,840 --> 01:14:01,760
Relax!

1148
01:14:05,319 --> 01:14:07,760
-Where are they?
-Goatface!

1149
01:14:12,000 --> 01:14:15,960
Song, you changed so fast.

1150
01:14:16,359 --> 01:14:18,880
And this mask?
Do you think you can scare me?

1151
01:14:22,199 --> 01:14:23,439
Hey.

1152
01:14:23,560 --> 01:14:25,439
Give it to me straight.

1153
01:14:25,520 --> 01:14:28,159
-Are you a ghost or a man?
-Ghost.

1154
01:14:29,640 --> 01:14:32,000
What a relief! I thought you were a man.

1155
01:14:34,840 --> 01:14:36,399
I'm screwed!

1156
01:14:38,399 --> 01:14:40,399
Where are you going? We haven't talked.

1157
01:14:43,439 --> 01:14:44,880
You're so stiff.

1158
01:15:35,840 --> 01:15:37,119
You're so stiff.

1159
01:16:03,960 --> 01:16:06,239
Hello, where you come from?

1160
01:16:06,439 --> 01:16:07,800
Chatting in English.

1161
01:16:17,199 --> 01:16:18,479
Why is it so hard?

1162
01:16:19,680 --> 01:16:21,000
I can go now!

1163
01:16:23,079 --> 01:16:24,640
Guava!

1164
01:16:26,960 --> 01:16:28,399
All this ghost nonsense,

1165
01:16:28,600 --> 01:16:31,239
we don't think it's real.
There's no such thing as ghost.

1166
01:16:32,039 --> 01:16:33,359
-They don't exist?
-No.

1167
01:16:33,439 --> 01:16:34,840
I'll catch one for you.

1168
01:16:34,960 --> 01:16:36,479
-Whatever.
-Yeah.

1169
01:16:38,039 --> 01:16:39,479
-“Taemybae.”
-Pardon?

1170
01:16:39,720 --> 01:16:41,600
-“Taemybae.”
-What?

1171
01:16:41,840 --> 01:16:44,159
-Take my bag.
-Dammit!

1172
01:16:44,479 --> 01:16:47,880
You should have just said that!

1173
01:16:48,359 --> 01:16:50,720
-It's the master's language.
-Then that's your business.

1174
01:16:50,880 --> 01:16:51,960
You wait here.

1175
01:16:54,000 --> 01:16:55,479
I'll catch you a ghost.

1176
01:16:56,199 --> 01:16:59,079
So you'll know they're real.

1177
01:17:02,000 --> 01:17:04,439
You're here. I've been looking.

1178
01:17:05,520 --> 01:17:06,680
I'm going to catch you.

1179
01:17:16,199 --> 01:17:20,960
You want to fight?

1180
01:17:22,479 --> 01:17:23,720
Do you want to fight me?

1181
01:17:31,279 --> 01:17:33,039
She's so strong.

1182
01:17:46,119 --> 01:17:48,279
How dare you do this to a ghost?

1183
01:17:48,840 --> 01:17:49,720
Damn!

1184
01:17:50,800 --> 01:17:52,199
Embarrassing.

1185
01:18:02,039 --> 01:18:03,439
Gosh!

1186
01:18:03,680 --> 01:18:05,840
You scared all the pigments
out of my face!

1187
01:18:07,800 --> 01:18:09,520
I'm not afraid of you, ghost.

1188
01:18:09,880 --> 01:18:11,239
-“Immanogho.”
-Pardon?

1189
01:18:11,359 --> 01:18:13,119
-“Immanogho.”
-What?

1190
01:18:13,239 --> 01:18:14,640
I'm not a ghost!

1191
01:18:15,119 --> 01:18:17,199
If you're not a ghost,
then what are you?

1192
01:18:17,800 --> 01:18:19,439
-What?
-"Imyomasta."

1193
01:18:19,760 --> 01:18:20,920
-Pardon?
-"Imyomasta."

1194
01:18:21,199 --> 01:18:22,880
-What did you say?
-I'm your master!

1195
01:18:23,000 --> 01:18:24,600
What master?

1196
01:18:26,000 --> 01:18:28,600
-I'm your master, not a ghost.
-How dare you!

1197
01:18:28,680 --> 01:18:30,359
I told you I'm your master.

1198
01:18:30,439 --> 01:18:32,880
What master? You're not a master.

1199
01:18:33,039 --> 01:18:35,439
You liar!
You're a ghost!

1200
01:18:47,880 --> 01:18:49,640
Master!

1201
01:18:52,640 --> 01:18:55,600
Why don't you just stomp me to death?

1202
01:18:55,760 --> 01:18:56,800
Fine.

1203
01:18:58,920 --> 01:19:00,479
I was being sarcastic.

1204
01:19:09,680 --> 01:19:11,479
-Hold this.
-Careful.

1205
01:19:11,560 --> 01:19:13,039
Careful!

1206
01:19:13,760 --> 01:19:16,560
Come on! Your legs work fine.
Why don't you help?

1207
01:19:16,880 --> 01:19:18,199
Stop complaining!

1208
01:19:18,439 --> 01:19:19,960
You're so good.

1209
01:19:24,760 --> 01:19:26,960
Father! Father!

1210
01:19:27,079 --> 01:19:28,399
We're damned!

1211
01:19:29,800 --> 01:19:33,600
Yeah, all those bowls are damned.
What's going on?

1212
01:19:33,720 --> 01:19:36,560
We're damned! I came to tell...
I forgot!

1213
01:19:36,800 --> 01:19:38,520
-What--
-I remembered!

1214
01:19:38,600 --> 01:19:42,359
The marble Buddha's head was cut off.

1215
01:19:43,960 --> 01:19:46,319
Hurry, Ood! He's here.

1216
01:19:46,399 --> 01:19:48,079
Hello, detective.

1217
01:19:48,159 --> 01:19:49,720
-Ood.
-Look!

1218
01:19:50,880 --> 01:19:52,199
Hello, detective.

1219
01:19:52,760 --> 01:19:55,239
Come sit here, fat ass.

1220
01:19:58,880 --> 01:20:00,279
What bring you here, Venerable?

1221
01:20:00,600 --> 01:20:02,039
I want to report a crime.

1222
01:20:02,359 --> 01:20:03,760
What happened?

1223
01:20:04,000 --> 01:20:07,720
I want to report that the marble
Buddha's head was cut off.

1224
01:20:07,840 --> 01:20:09,840
When did that happened?

1225
01:20:10,319 --> 01:20:12,720
-What time, Ood?
-Late at night.

1226
01:20:13,039 --> 01:20:14,319
What time exactly?

1227
01:20:14,439 --> 01:20:15,840
-Around seven.
-That was late?

1228
01:20:15,920 --> 01:20:16,920
-Eight?
-Don't lie.

1229
01:20:17,039 --> 01:20:17,960
-Nine.
-Don't...

1230
01:20:18,039 --> 01:20:19,319
-Ten.
-Behave!

1231
01:20:19,520 --> 01:20:20,640
Eleven.

1232
01:20:21,760 --> 01:20:22,960
Well, I think

1233
01:20:23,119 --> 01:20:25,880
you two should have a talk
before filing a report.

1234
01:20:26,479 --> 01:20:27,760
My face's all wet.

1235
01:20:29,119 --> 01:20:31,920
The marble Buddha's head was cut off.

1236
01:20:32,359 --> 01:20:34,479
And we lost ten...

1237
01:20:38,000 --> 01:20:41,279
Just ten Bahts?
You don't have to file a report.

1238
01:20:41,399 --> 01:20:43,158
I can give it to you.

1239
01:20:43,479 --> 01:20:47,399
May Buddha bless you.
You're so generous.

1240
01:20:47,840 --> 01:20:50,239
But that's a lot of money.

1241
01:20:50,479 --> 01:20:53,359
How is that a lot of money?

1242
01:20:53,760 --> 01:20:55,239
Ten alms-bowls full of money.

1243
01:20:55,399 --> 01:20:58,279
That's 75,000 Bahts in total.

1244
01:20:58,720 --> 01:21:00,439
Yeah, they're all gone.

1245
01:21:00,840 --> 01:21:02,800
Let's talk about the Buddha head.

1246
01:21:03,000 --> 01:21:04,439
How many were cut off?

1247
01:21:04,720 --> 01:21:09,119
Just one. He's not the great
serpent with eight heads.

1248
01:21:09,920 --> 01:21:10,840
Hello?

1249
01:21:11,439 --> 01:21:13,319
Yes. I'm sorry, my friend.

1250
01:21:13,920 --> 01:21:16,039
You go to the warehouse.

1251
01:21:17,600 --> 01:21:19,279
So we can exchange.

1252
01:21:20,520 --> 01:21:22,199
Give me some time to prepare.

1253
01:21:23,119 --> 01:21:24,039
Okay.

1254
01:21:26,600 --> 01:21:28,600
Bye-bye!

1255
01:21:40,399 --> 01:21:41,920
This is Phra Noi.

1256
01:21:43,439 --> 01:21:44,319
Yes.

1257
01:21:45,520 --> 01:21:47,359
I need your help.

1258
01:21:47,800 --> 01:21:50,359
I need you to find
the head of the marble Buddha.

1259
01:21:52,880 --> 01:21:55,760
It's the least we can do
to protect our religion.

1260
01:21:56,159 --> 01:21:58,159
And that's the way to fight back.

1261
01:22:01,159 --> 01:22:02,199
May Buddha bless you.

1262
01:22:27,279 --> 01:22:28,199
Phra Noi!

1263
01:22:29,319 --> 01:22:30,159
Phra Noi!

1264
01:22:31,000 --> 01:22:34,279
Why are you revving up
your motorcycle so loud?

1265
01:22:34,840 --> 01:22:36,720
It's improper.

1266
01:22:38,199 --> 01:22:40,560
Hey! The fact that you're making noise,

1267
01:22:40,920 --> 01:22:44,600
it means that your mind is not at peace.

1268
01:22:45,159 --> 01:22:46,199
Do you understand?

1269
01:22:49,079 --> 01:22:50,760
I'm telling you...

1270
01:22:52,119 --> 01:22:53,319
This is peace.

1271
01:22:58,399 --> 01:22:59,279
Venerable!

1272
01:23:00,560 --> 01:23:01,920
I need your help.

1273
01:23:02,159 --> 01:23:03,600
What's the matter, Phra Noi?

1274
01:23:03,680 --> 01:23:06,039
We have to bring back
the marble Buddha's head.

1275
01:23:06,279 --> 01:23:08,600
Well, I'm in.

1276
01:23:09,680 --> 01:23:10,920
Em and Ood too.

1277
01:23:53,800 --> 01:23:56,399
I heard you take orders here?

1278
01:23:56,560 --> 01:23:58,359
-What type of order?
-Buddha statues.

1279
01:23:58,840 --> 01:23:59,920
Who told you?

1280
01:24:00,159 --> 01:24:02,239
Lek, the owner of the drug called
Jiu Jeng Pushen Jiao Nang.

1281
01:24:02,319 --> 01:24:05,319
-Do you know Master Tossaporn?
-Master Tossaporn?

1282
01:24:08,640 --> 01:24:10,159
Go ahead.

1283
01:24:10,880 --> 01:24:13,600
There's a newfound Buddha statue
floating up down the river.

1284
01:24:14,000 --> 01:24:15,600
The locals call him Father Nim.

1285
01:24:16,199 --> 01:24:17,279
I need the whole statue.

1286
01:24:18,640 --> 01:24:19,800
Father Nim.

1287
01:24:35,600 --> 01:24:37,319
My goodness!

1288
01:24:40,079 --> 01:24:43,439
It's too big!
Can we cut off just the head?

1289
01:24:43,600 --> 01:24:45,520
No! They want the whole statue.

1290
01:24:47,039 --> 01:24:48,720
It's not that hard.

1291
01:24:49,319 --> 01:24:51,439
We cut it into three pieces.

1292
01:24:51,640 --> 01:24:53,119
Then put them back on.

1293
01:24:54,920 --> 01:24:56,840
No! That means defects!

1294
01:24:57,000 --> 01:24:57,840
Does it?

1295
01:24:58,520 --> 01:25:01,880
What do we do?
It's too big for us to carry.

1296
01:25:02,640 --> 01:25:05,439
I have a wicked idea.
Stuff like this, leave it to me.

1297
01:25:05,840 --> 01:25:08,800
We singe it with a candle
to make it lightweight.

1298
01:25:09,119 --> 01:25:12,239
Then we put a stick through the bottom
and carry it with no problem.

1299
01:25:13,560 --> 01:25:15,479
This is a Buddha statue, not a corn dog.

1300
01:25:15,600 --> 01:25:17,359
Believe me. I know the tricks.

1301
01:25:18,000 --> 01:25:20,039
-Really?
-Try it.

1302
01:25:21,399 --> 01:25:22,720
Trust me.

1303
01:25:24,520 --> 01:25:25,680
Why is it so big though?

1304
01:25:29,119 --> 01:25:31,399
Sadhu...

1305
01:25:36,920 --> 01:25:39,600
There're a lot of mosquitoes.

1306
01:25:39,960 --> 01:25:42,079
Oh...

1307
01:25:42,960 --> 01:25:43,840
What's that?

1308
01:25:44,479 --> 01:25:47,680
I think the abbot is fast asleep
and purrs in his sleep.

1309
01:25:47,760 --> 01:25:50,199
So we have nothing to worry about!

1310
01:25:50,720 --> 01:25:52,520
-Let's carry it.
-Yeah.

1311
01:25:52,600 --> 01:25:54,520
-Put a stick through the bottom?
-No.

1312
01:25:54,800 --> 01:25:56,199
Just carry it.

1313
01:25:57,680 --> 01:26:00,159
Father Nim is so fleshy.

1314
01:26:00,760 --> 01:26:02,600
Almost like human.

1315
01:26:02,760 --> 01:26:03,640
Yeah!

1316
01:26:04,159 --> 01:26:05,840
Oh...

1317
01:26:06,159 --> 01:26:08,359
Let's go! The abbot's probably awake!

1318
01:26:08,479 --> 01:26:10,199
Come on! Open the door!

1319
01:26:10,319 --> 01:26:11,640
Why does he keep purring?

1320
01:26:16,079 --> 01:26:17,319
Hurry up!

1321
01:26:20,920 --> 01:26:22,199
Play some music.

1322
01:26:38,079 --> 01:26:40,520
Father Nim!

1323
01:26:41,279 --> 01:26:43,479
My dad's going to be so rich.

1324
01:26:43,840 --> 01:26:46,960
-But he's really fleshy.
-That's why he floated.

1325
01:26:49,680 --> 01:26:51,119
Why are you growling?

1326
01:26:51,439 --> 01:26:53,079
Let's show it to my dad.

1327
01:26:53,199 --> 01:26:54,279
Right.

1328
01:27:06,039 --> 01:27:08,319
Hello, Phra Noi.

1329
01:27:08,720 --> 01:27:09,760
This is me, Phra Yokyek.

1330
01:27:11,000 --> 01:27:14,039
I'm not sure. It was dark when we left.

1331
01:27:14,760 --> 01:27:18,840
But I know that they sang
Bualoi on the way here.

1332
01:27:19,239 --> 01:27:22,600
I think you should sing Bualoi
when you leave the temple.

1333
01:27:22,720 --> 01:27:25,720
I remembered which parts
they turned left and right.

1334
01:27:25,952 --> 01:27:26,872
Okay?

1335
01:27:27,271 --> 01:27:28,119
Right.

1336
01:27:28,680 --> 01:27:30,279
I have to go now.

1337
01:27:30,920 --> 01:27:31,800
They're back.

1338
01:27:37,520 --> 01:27:39,199
Where is Father Nim?

1339
01:27:40,199 --> 01:27:42,800
It's so majestic!

1340
01:27:43,359 --> 01:27:44,239
Father Nim.

1341
01:27:45,479 --> 01:27:47,039
He's fleshy!

1342
01:27:47,439 --> 01:27:48,800
Is this a statue or a bun?

1343
01:27:49,000 --> 01:27:50,119
-Statue.
-Buddha statue?

1344
01:27:50,239 --> 01:27:52,600
-Authentic one.
-Okay. Great.

1345
01:27:52,720 --> 01:27:54,119
You did a great job.

1346
01:27:54,239 --> 01:27:56,159
This is the first time
you accomplished something.

1347
01:27:56,239 --> 01:27:58,920
-Close the door.
-Close it.

1348
01:28:00,119 --> 01:28:01,039
Careful.

1349
01:28:10,079 --> 01:28:12,680
Cross the bridge and go straight.

1350
01:28:19,000 --> 01:28:21,319
Bualoi, my dear friend

1351
01:28:21,640 --> 01:28:24,039
Why did you have to leave me so soon?

1352
01:28:24,800 --> 01:28:29,920
Bualoi, where are you now?
Do know how I miss you

1353
01:28:30,439 --> 01:28:32,920
Bualoi

1354
01:28:33,239 --> 01:28:34,159
Bualoi!

1355
01:28:35,000 --> 01:28:36,159
Wait for me!

1356
01:28:36,680 --> 01:28:40,079
After "how I miss you, Bualoi,"
you'll see a roundabout.

1357
01:28:40,279 --> 01:28:42,399
Keep to the right and straight ahead.

1358
01:28:42,600 --> 01:28:47,920
Bualoi was a young lad with lazy eyes
A hunchback and awkward nature

1359
01:28:48,079 --> 01:28:53,479
He might be far from beautiful
But he had a heart of gold

1360
01:28:53,560 --> 01:28:59,319
He's with you when you're lonely
He cooked for you when you're hungry

1361
01:28:59,399 --> 01:29:02,479
He took care of you when you're weary

1362
01:29:02,560 --> 01:29:05,720
Bringing you medicine to ease your pain

1363
01:29:05,800 --> 01:29:08,119
Bualoi was drafted

1364
01:29:08,199 --> 01:29:11,439
Though handicapped
He's still can be a soldier

1365
01:29:11,640 --> 01:29:15,000
Wait for me!
I'm going to out speed you, watch me!

1366
01:29:15,520 --> 01:29:17,159
Go straight, Phra Noi.

1367
01:29:17,319 --> 01:29:20,039
After the solo finishes, you'll be here.

1368
01:29:20,239 --> 01:29:22,760
He could put up with anything

1369
01:29:22,880 --> 01:29:25,319
He's helpful to those in need

1370
01:29:25,479 --> 01:29:29,039
He shared your sufferings
Not just in for his happiness

1371
01:29:31,640 --> 01:29:33,479
Okay.

1372
01:29:33,880 --> 01:29:34,920
Bye-bye.

1373
01:29:39,960 --> 01:29:42,439
Boss! Boss!

1374
01:29:42,600 --> 01:29:44,520
We're going to be super rich!

1375
01:29:45,199 --> 01:29:47,119
-They came to deliver the statue.
-Where?

1376
01:29:47,319 --> 01:29:50,039
-Outside. Give me your hand.
-My hand is here.

1377
01:29:50,119 --> 01:29:52,199
-No wonder it doesn't have nail.
-They fell off.

1378
01:29:52,439 --> 01:29:55,640
-Sorry. That's why it's flabby.
-They fell off.

1379
01:29:56,960 --> 01:29:58,600
Here comes the money!

1380
01:30:07,720 --> 01:30:11,199
Money? That's prison! Let's go now!

1381
01:30:12,319 --> 01:30:13,960
Who invited them?

1382
01:30:14,239 --> 01:30:15,680
Wait for me, assholes!

1383
01:30:27,319 --> 01:30:28,279
Hey!

1384
01:30:28,439 --> 01:30:30,079
Run! Father! Run!

1385
01:30:30,319 --> 01:30:32,279
-What?
-Come on!

1386
01:30:32,359 --> 01:30:35,920
-You should stay there.
-Don't pull! We don't have undies.

1387
01:30:37,880 --> 01:30:38,840
This way!

1388
01:30:54,479 --> 01:30:55,760
Jerk!

1389
01:30:56,159 --> 01:30:58,359
-What?
-You startled me!

1390
01:31:04,800 --> 01:31:05,720
Got a rope?

1391
01:31:07,279 --> 01:31:08,960
Damn! I'm so amazing!

1392
01:31:10,560 --> 01:31:11,720
Take this!

1393
01:31:19,039 --> 01:31:20,479
Do you want to fight?

1394
01:31:21,359 --> 01:31:22,199
Come on!

1395
01:31:27,039 --> 01:31:28,319
Damn!

1396
01:31:28,640 --> 01:31:31,319
I still want to fly my kites!

1397
01:31:34,560 --> 01:31:35,680
Back off!

1398
01:31:37,159 --> 01:31:38,239
Come!

1399
01:31:43,119 --> 01:31:44,319
I'll give you another try.

1400
01:31:45,479 --> 01:31:46,439
Come!

1401
01:31:50,479 --> 01:31:52,279
This is your last chance.

1402
01:31:53,760 --> 01:31:55,279
I'm not going to let you walk away.

1403
01:32:07,840 --> 01:32:08,960
Who hit me?

1404
01:32:23,520 --> 01:32:25,039
Damn! That hurts!

1405
01:32:38,560 --> 01:32:41,760
Carabao Daeng contains B12.
Drink it to nourish your brain.

1406
01:32:45,560 --> 01:32:47,800
Spread out and search this whole place.

1407
01:32:52,239 --> 01:32:53,439
What do we do?

1408
01:32:59,880 --> 01:33:02,079
Here we go.

1409
01:33:07,640 --> 01:33:10,000
Follow me if you don't want to get caught.

1410
01:33:15,279 --> 01:33:18,279
-Look thoroughly.
-I found it.

1411
01:33:18,880 --> 01:33:20,359
Unlimited faith!

1412
01:33:20,920 --> 01:33:23,159
Your number one follower is here to help!

1413
01:33:23,239 --> 01:33:26,279
Thank you. Well done!

1414
01:33:28,640 --> 01:33:29,760
You're dead!

1415
01:33:30,800 --> 01:33:31,720
Don't hit me.

1416
01:33:43,840 --> 01:33:45,359
I didn't do it. You did it.

1417
01:33:48,640 --> 01:33:49,880
Cool moves.

1418
01:33:50,279 --> 01:33:52,159
Search! Search!

1419
01:33:53,600 --> 01:33:56,560
What? You're not funny anymore?

1420
01:33:56,760 --> 01:33:58,960
-Who wants to be rich?
-I do. I do.

1421
01:34:00,239 --> 01:34:01,479
Gun me like this.

1422
01:34:01,560 --> 01:34:03,520
If anything happens, nobody will laugh.

1423
01:34:04,359 --> 01:34:05,520
Calm down.

1424
01:34:05,880 --> 01:34:08,039
Don't come any closer, or I shoot!

1425
01:34:08,439 --> 01:34:10,840
Killing is a sin.
It's against the first precept.

1426
01:34:11,199 --> 01:34:13,600
This is a monk, not an animal.

1427
01:34:15,439 --> 01:34:16,760
Please put the gun down.

1428
01:34:17,279 --> 01:34:19,720
It's never too late.
You can still be forgiven.

1429
01:34:20,119 --> 01:34:23,920
Angulimala is a ruthless murderer.
But he quits and turns to Dharma.

1430
01:34:24,239 --> 01:34:26,800
He's ordained and becomes enlightened.

1431
01:34:27,399 --> 01:34:28,439
That's nonsense.

1432
01:34:30,199 --> 01:34:32,560
Have you ever heard the story
about a python and a chicken?

1433
01:34:33,439 --> 01:34:36,880
A python coils around an egg
without knowing that it's a chicken egg.

1434
01:34:37,199 --> 01:34:39,239
Finally a baby chicken
hatches out of the egg.

1435
01:34:39,640 --> 01:34:41,279
The python, however,
doesn't eat the baby.

1436
01:34:41,640 --> 01:34:43,079
considering the baby her own child.

1437
01:34:43,159 --> 01:34:46,079
The baby is not afraid of the python,
considering her mother.

1438
01:34:46,720 --> 01:34:48,199
They live together.

1439
01:34:48,840 --> 01:34:52,000
One day, the python and the chicken
go separate ways to find food.

1440
01:34:52,239 --> 01:34:54,159
The chicken runs into a fox.

1441
01:34:54,600 --> 01:34:57,720
The chicken says, "May all beings
be free from exploiting each other."

1442
01:34:57,960 --> 01:34:59,239
The fox doesn't listen.

1443
01:34:59,399 --> 01:35:01,319
"Chickens are food. I must eat it"

1444
01:35:02,239 --> 01:35:05,680
The chicken has an idea.
"Oh, my mother is a serpent!"

1445
01:35:06,119 --> 01:35:08,640
The chicken jumps at the fox
and coils it to death!

1446
01:35:21,079 --> 01:35:22,920
And that is how things are.

1447
01:35:23,920 --> 01:35:25,159
Everybody's so touched.

1448
01:35:25,239 --> 01:35:26,319
Phra Noi.

1449
01:35:26,960 --> 01:35:28,560
How can a chicken coil up the fox?

1450
01:35:31,479 --> 01:35:33,079
Come!

1451
01:35:36,399 --> 01:35:37,279
Hey!

1452
01:35:38,920 --> 01:35:41,359
You're amazed, right?

1453
01:35:41,920 --> 01:35:43,399
Amazed by me!

1454
01:35:43,479 --> 01:35:45,279
Amazed at your accent.

1455
01:35:45,479 --> 01:35:46,920
-Shut up!
-Venerable!

1456
01:35:47,159 --> 01:35:48,239
Don't worry about atama.

1457
01:35:48,311 --> 01:35:49,199
No!

1458
01:35:49,359 --> 01:35:51,039
Venerable, don't worry about me!

1459
01:35:51,159 --> 01:35:52,760
How can I not, my friend?

1460
01:35:56,119 --> 01:35:59,439
Just shoot him! Don't worry about me!
Come on!

1461
01:35:59,680 --> 01:36:02,479
-Shoot him!
-Stop struggling or I hit you in the head.

1462
01:36:05,279 --> 01:36:07,880
Song! Let the police do his job!

1463
01:36:08,079 --> 01:36:09,760
Why are you stuffing a Buddha statue?

1464
01:36:10,640 --> 01:36:11,600
Shoot him!

1465
01:36:13,479 --> 01:36:14,560
No!

1466
01:36:15,159 --> 01:36:18,239
You not only look alike,
but are also stupid!

1467
01:36:22,760 --> 01:36:26,359
Song!

1468
01:36:33,800 --> 01:36:36,000
No! Ood!

1469
01:36:37,119 --> 01:36:38,520
-Em!
-Em!

1470
01:36:38,600 --> 01:36:39,439
Em!

1471
01:36:42,000 --> 01:36:43,079
I'm screwed!

1472
01:36:50,880 --> 01:36:53,159
Not dead, but close enough.

1473
01:36:53,319 --> 01:36:55,199
Is this what you want?

1474
01:36:56,560 --> 01:36:58,920
Damn! Every one of your bullets hit me!

1475
01:36:59,119 --> 01:37:00,199
Such a good shot!

1476
01:37:00,359 --> 01:37:02,680
I heard of spitting lies
with the amulet in a mouth.

1477
01:37:03,239 --> 01:37:05,000
But you're spitting bullets!

1478
01:37:06,279 --> 01:37:07,800
Song! You are so damn stupid!

1479
01:37:10,520 --> 01:37:11,399
Hey!

1480
01:37:12,680 --> 01:37:15,359
-Avenge him for me.
-Sure.

1481
01:37:19,000 --> 01:37:21,399
-Is he dead?
-What's wrong with you people?

1482
01:37:25,079 --> 01:37:27,800
Why are you handcuffing me?
I didn't do anything wrong.

1483
01:37:28,319 --> 01:37:30,760
-You're caught red-handed.
-I did nothing wrong!

1484
01:37:31,279 --> 01:37:32,640
-Let's go.
-You did nothing wrong?

1485
01:37:32,720 --> 01:37:34,479
-Commander...
-Let me go.

1486
01:37:34,560 --> 01:37:36,399
-...avenge him for me.
-Sure.

1487
01:37:36,479 --> 01:37:38,319
-Thank you!
-I did nothing wrong!

1488
01:37:38,439 --> 01:37:41,159
-Will they shoot me again?
-Let me go!

1489
01:37:44,920 --> 01:37:46,520
Stop growling at us! Move!

1490
01:37:53,439 --> 01:37:55,319
A Buddha statue in a distress posture.

1491
01:37:57,720 --> 01:37:59,000
Father!

1492
01:38:03,079 --> 01:38:05,279
-Hello!
-I'm so glad!

1493
01:38:05,359 --> 01:38:06,960
-Father!
-There! There!

1494
01:38:08,000 --> 01:38:09,720
Thank you, Ad.

1495
01:38:09,920 --> 01:38:12,279
-It's nothing, Venerable. We're friends.
-Right.

1496
01:38:12,720 --> 01:38:16,720
Do you know the way out?
You can sing Bualoi backwards.

1497
01:38:18,000 --> 01:38:19,720
What do we do?

1498
01:38:19,840 --> 01:38:22,159
-You're funny, Venerable.
-Yeah, right.

1499
01:38:23,319 --> 01:38:24,720
Loibua!

1500
01:38:25,760 --> 01:38:28,560
I think we'd better not.
Let's go eat noodles!

1501
01:38:29,199 --> 01:38:30,600
-And rice with pork too.
-Yeah.

1502
01:38:32,079 --> 01:38:32,920
Thank you.

1503
01:38:56,520 --> 01:38:57,880
Hurry up! We'll be late!

1504
01:38:58,479 --> 01:38:59,720
Please get in.

1505
01:38:59,840 --> 01:39:01,279
Can I sit with you?

1506
01:39:01,359 --> 01:39:04,239
-Come in, come in.
-Scooch over.

1507
01:39:06,000 --> 01:39:07,720
Close the doors.

1508
01:39:07,880 --> 01:39:08,800
Come on.

1509
01:39:08,920 --> 01:39:09,960
Close the back doors.

1510
01:39:10,800 --> 01:39:13,159
-We're ready. Let's go.
-Yeah.

1511
01:39:15,079 --> 01:39:16,760
-Hey!
-What?

1512
01:39:16,920 --> 01:39:20,600
-Are you really going to do that?
-I'm wearing a hat, I'm not joking.

1513
01:39:20,720 --> 01:39:23,840
It's nothing to do with hat.
If you do it, I hit you real hard.

1514
01:39:24,119 --> 01:39:26,680
Let's go. We have to pick up another one.

1515
01:39:29,880 --> 01:39:31,760
You just hit me in the groin! You...

1516
01:39:37,920 --> 01:39:40,319
-It's here.
-Stop grabbing mine.

1517
01:39:50,520 --> 01:39:51,680
What?

1518
01:39:51,880 --> 01:39:55,000
I don't think we should get in.
There are a lot of dogs.

1519
01:39:57,239 --> 01:39:58,720
Dogs don't bite monks.

1520
01:39:58,800 --> 01:40:01,279
They know who's good and who's bad.

1521
01:40:01,439 --> 01:40:03,039
They don't bite monks, right?

1522
01:40:03,239 --> 01:40:05,560
-Right.
-But I'm not a monk. What should I do?

1523
01:40:05,680 --> 01:40:06,560
I'm not a monk.

1524
01:40:06,680 --> 01:40:09,720
Tell them you're a temple boy.
They know that, they won't bite.

1525
01:40:09,800 --> 01:40:12,039
-Follow me.
-Yeah, they won’t bite.

1526
01:40:15,079 --> 01:40:16,039
Go!

1527
01:40:38,279 --> 01:40:39,239
Oh...

1528
01:40:40,439 --> 01:40:42,640
dogs really don't bite monks.

1529
01:40:42,720 --> 01:40:44,800
True. They just chewed off our robes.

1530
01:40:46,439 --> 01:40:48,520
Hey! Song! Song!

1531
01:40:49,119 --> 01:40:50,800
Hey! Goonsong!

1532
01:41:04,880 --> 01:41:06,800
Don't believe what you see.

1533
01:41:07,159 --> 01:41:09,319
Don't believe what you hear.

1534
01:41:09,520 --> 01:41:12,000
Don't believe that dogs don't bite monks.

1535
01:41:12,600 --> 01:41:14,840
This is proof.

1536
01:41:15,079 --> 01:41:16,640
So don't believe the things you see

1537
01:41:16,720 --> 01:41:18,159
and don't believe the things you hear

1538
01:41:18,239 --> 01:41:21,600
and don't believe
that dogs don't bite monks.

1539
01:41:23,680 --> 01:41:24,840
May Buddha bless you.

1540
01:41:29,079 --> 01:41:31,079
Subtitle translation by Suganya Pankote

